<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Student Learning Portal</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #eef7ff;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #0066cc;
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: 30px auto;
            background-color: white;
            padding: 25px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px gray;
        }

        h2 {
            color: #0066cc;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        button {
            background-color: #0066cc;
            color: white;
            padding: 12px 25px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 18px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #004c99;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Student Learning Portal</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <h2 id="title">Welcome Students!</h2>

        <p id="content">
            Education is the key to success. Learning new skills and gaining knowledge
            helps students achieve their goals and build a bright future.
        </p>

        <button onclick="changeContent()">
            Learn More
        </button>
    </div>

    <script>
        function changeContent() {
            document.getElementById("title").textContent =
            "Importance of Continuous Learning";

            document.getElementById("content").textContent =
            "Continuous learning improves knowledge, develops problem-solving skills, boosts confidence, and prepares students for future challenges. Every day is an opportunity to learn something new.";
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
